modules.description: Provides functions for establishing database connections via URI, executing parameterized queries, and retrieving results as typed tuples. Works with OCaml's first-class modules, database-specific drivers, and SQL-like query structures. Used to build database-agnostic applications that dynamically adapt to different backends like PostgreSQL or MySQL.

Loads database drivers from shared libraries using dynamic linking. Supports loading and initializing drivers at runtime, enabling flexible database connectivity. Used to integrate various database backends without recompiling the application.
